<p>I have a Symfony2 project with one domain and one subdomain.</p>  <p>The main domain has SSL, the subdomain doesn't.</p>  <p>When I call some ajax requests to the main domain, the browser console shows me this message: </p>  <blockquote>   <p>No 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin' header is present on the requested   resource. Origin 'null' is therefore not allowed access.</p> </blockquote>  <p>I try adding headers to that requests in controllers like this:</p>  <pre><code>    $responseHeaders = $response-&gt;headers;      $responseHeaders-&gt;set('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'origin, content-type, accept');     $responseHeaders-&gt;set('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');     $responseHeaders-&gt;set('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'POST, GET'); </code></pre>  <p>How can I solve this?</p>